# Linux add Vloume 
1. Create Instance 
2. Connect with putty 
3. Select Volume And Attache this volume from AWS Action 
Note: before atach volume check  Instance Name and Device name
4. Now Lunux open putty 
5. Run lsblk Check this volume 
out put : <br>
xvdz     202:6400  0   30G  0 disk 
6. Format the new volume 
sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdz
7. Create a mount point
sudo mkdir /mnt/volume
8. Mount this volume 
sudo mount /dev/xvdz /mnt/volume
9. Verify Itâ€™s Mounted
df -h
10. Mount Automatically on Reboot 
10.1 . Get the UUID:
11. Edit /etc/fstab:
UUID=9298fff1-b891-4824-84b0-fd59f5ab032f /mnt/volume ext4 defaults,nofail 0 2
12. Test your /etc/fstab configuration:
sudo mount -a
13. Verify the mount:
df -h | grep /mnt/volume






